name: Sara Phillips - Better When It Ends.

metadata.description:
Better When It Ends. is an incredibly important song to me, written about one of the toughest experiences of my life. 
I hope it speaks to you in some way. 


I woke up screaming out loud
pulled all your pictures down
set fire to everything inside my room
that smells like you 
and I woke up screaming out loud

and now I don't look back
and I don't look down
now when I'm flying 
over your town
with all of my bruises
almost all faded out

cause you're the kind of dream
that's better when it ends
I should have seen it 
coming from back then
when I thought love meant hurting
you were my favorite person
but you're the kind of dream
that's better when it -

I woke up screaming your name
and I called but you never came
I drowned while you watched from the sand
with my life in your hands 
and a smile on your face

but now I don't look back 
and I don't look down
now when I'm flying 
over your town
with all of my bruises
almost all faded out

cause you're the kind of dream
that's better when it ends
I should have seen it 
coming from back then
when I thought love meant hurting
you were my favorite person
but you're the kind of dream
that's better when it ends.
